# SASS Conventions

## Architecture (never deviate)

```
src/sass/
├── _variables.scss      # Single source of tokens
├── _bootstrap.scss      # Bootstrap config (override before @import)
├── main.scss            # Orchestrator — edit here to enable a partial
├── admin.scss           # WP/Symfony back-office styles (separate bundle)
├── mixins/              # One file per mixin, aggregated via mixins.scss
├── components/          # Reusable UI bricks (.btn, .alert, .modal...)
│   ├── forms/           # Inputs, selects, checkboxes, radios, file, datepicker
│   └── layouts/         # ACF block layout styles — file per block, prefix `b-*`
├── layouts/             # header, footer, commons, layout (aggregator for b-*)
└── pages/               # Page-specific styles
```

Creating a new SCSS file ⇒ **always** add it to `main.scss` in the proper section.

## Variables & tokens — `_variables.scss`

Before writing any color or size, check `_variables.scss`. Canonical keys:

**Colors** (raw + semantic) :
- Raw palette: project-named (e.g. `$blue`, `$light-blue`, `$dark-grey`, `$grey-10`…`$grey-50`, `$red`, `$green`, `$yellow`, `$orange`, `$white`, `$black`, `$beige`)
- Semantic: `$primary`, `$secondary`, `$tertiary`, `$success`, `$info`, `$warning`, `$danger`
- Surfaces: `$text-color`, `$body-color`, `$border-color`, `$input-color`
- Contrast: `$min-contrast-ratio` (default 2.5 — aim for 4.5 on body text)

**Sizes:** `$btn-height: 50px`, `$input-height: 50px`, `$input-height-lg: 60px`, `$grid-gutter-width: 24-32px` (project-dependent)

**Fonts:** `$font-family-base` (primary), `$font-family-alt` (optional secondary), `$font-size-base: 1rem`, `$font-size-base-px` (computed via `strip-unit` for `rem()`)

**Breakpoints:** 5-breakpoint map
```scss
$grid-breakpoints: (
  xs: 0,
  sm: 768px,
  md: 1024px,
  lg: 1270px,   // intentionally < 1280 (Edge on Windows)
  xl: 1430px    // may vary between projects (1430–1445px)
) !default;
```

**Containers:** `$container-max-widths` with `sm: 1215px, md: 1220px, lg: 1320px, xl: 1400px` (typical; project-specific)

## Mixins — full list and usage

Located in `src/sass/mixins/`. Imported via `mixins.scss`.

| Mixin / function | Signature | Typical usage |
|---|---|---|
| `rem()` **function** | `rem($px)` | `font-size: rem(18px);` |
| `rem()` **mixin** (2 args+) | `@include rem($prop, $values...)` | `@include rem(padding, 20px 10px);` — outputs both `px` fallback and `rem` |
| `min()` / `max()` | `@include max(md) { … }` | media queries (desktop-first preferred) |
| `ratio()` | `@include ratio(16, 9)` | aspect-ratio boxes |
| `bgco` / `bgci` / `bgc` | background helpers | `background-size: cover` + centering + fallbacks |
| `circle()` | `@include circle(40px)` | round shapes |
| `icon()` | `@include icon(name, before|after)` | iconfont glyph injection |
| `font-face()` | web-font registration | in `_fonts.scss` |
| `burger` / `burger-to-cross` | menu burger animations | in `_menu.scss` |
| `clearfix()` | legacy float clearing | rarely used |
| `strip-unit()` | `strip-unit(16px)` → `16` | internal to `rem()` |

⚠️ There is **no** `maxlines()` / line-clamp mixin — use raw `-webkit-line-clamp` + `display: -webkit-box` where needed.

## Kebab-case naming + prefixes (full list)

| Prefix | Use | Examples |
|---|---|---|
| `header-*`, `footer-*` | Layouts | `header-wrap`, `header-logo`, `footer-nav-title` |
| `btn-*` | Buttons | `btn-primary`, `btn-link`, `btn-menu`, `btn-search`, `btn-outline-primary`, `btn-xs-full`, `btn-icon-left`, `btn-arrow-right-link` |
| `default-*` | Default elements (sections, titles, cards) | `default-section`, `default-alt-section`, `default-title`, `default-h2-title`, `default-suptitle`, `default-tag`, `default-card`, `default-breadcrumb` |
| `article-*` | Article / blog content | `article-head-section`, `article-tag`, `article-intro` |
| `cms-*` | CMS-injected (WYSIWYG) content | `cms-content` |
| `b-*` | **ACF block layout styles** (in `components/layouts/`) — one file per Flexible Content layout | `b-head`, `b-accordion`, `b-newsletter`, `b-timeline`, `b-img-text` |
| `icon-*` | Iconfont glyph classes (generated by Gulp `iconfont` task) | `icon-search`, `icon-arrow-right`, `icon-close` |
| `a11y-*` | Responsive a11y visibility (complements Bootstrap `d-*`) | `a11y-md`, `a11y-lg-inverse` |
| `is-*` | Component states | `is-active`, `is-open`, `is-loading`, `is-expanded`, `is-collapsed` |
| `has-*` | Validation / presence state | `has-error`, `has-success` |
| `js-*` | JS hook ONLY — never styled in CSS | `js-accordion`, `js-copy-url`, `js-default-sort` |
| `splide__*` / `swiper-*` | Third-party library classes — keep as-is | `splide__track`, `swiper-pagination` |
| `visually-hidden`, `visually-hidden-focusable` | a11y helpers | skip link, icon-only button labels |

## Examples

```scss
// ❌ BAD
.my-button {
  color: #003cff;
  font-size: 18px;
  padding: 10px;
  @media (min-width: 768px) { padding: 20px; }
}

// ✅ GOOD (desktop-first)
.btn-primary {
  color: $tertiary;
  font-size: rem(18px);
  @include rem(padding, 10px);
  @include max(sm) { @include rem(padding, 8px); }
}

// ✅ ACF block layout file: components/layouts/b-text-image-fifty.scss
.b-text-image-fifty {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
  gap: $grid-gutter-width;
  @include max(md) { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
}
```
